; ── Peer-dependency policy ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
; legacy-peer-deps is DELIBERATE, not a shortcut. This app is 100% App Router, so at runtime BOTH
; the server and the client bundles use Next.js 15's VENDORED React 19 — the react@18 declared in
; package.json only serves types and non-app tooling. That makes the peer wall unsolvable at any
; single declared version:
;   · @react-three/fiber@9 + drei@10 (required: R3F v8 reads React-18 internals that vendored
;     React 19 removed -> "Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'ReactCurrentBatchConfig')")
;     declare peers react >=19.
;   · react-day-picker@8 (shadcn calendar) declares peers react <=18.
; Whichever react we declare, one of them refuses a strict install. Runtime compatibility is
; verified in scripts/assembly-timeline.test.ts + the production build; remove this flag only when
; react-day-picker is migrated to v9 and react/react-dom are bumped to ^19 together.
legacy-peer-deps=true
